  version: {fileID: 11400000, guid: f0e13320f8bc1254f8bca32b62d9305b, type: 2}
  description: 
  chapters:
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Nehemiah Prays for His People'
      title: Nehemiah Prays for His People
      number: 1
      content: 'The words of Nehemiah the son of Hachaliah.It came to pass in the
        month of Chislev, in the twentieth year, as I was in Shushan the citadel, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'that Hanani one of my brethren came with men from Judah; and I asked
        them concerning the Jews who had escaped, who had survived the captivity,
        and concerning Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "And they said to me, \u201CThe survivors who are left from the captivity
        in the province are there in great distress and reproach. The wall of Jerusalem
        is also broken down, and its gates are burned with fire.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: So it was, when I heard these words, that I sat down and wept, and
        mourned for  many days; I was fasting and praying before the God of heaven.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "And I said: \u201CI pray, Lord God of heaven, O great and awesome
        God, You who keep Your covenant and mercy with those who love You and observe
        Your commandments, "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "please let Your ear be attentive and Your eyes open, that You may
        hear the prayer of Your servant which I pray before You now, day and night,
        for the children of Israel Your servants, and confess the sins of the children
        of Israel which we have sinned against You. Both my father\u2019s house and
        I have sinned. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'We have acted very corruptly against You, and have not kept the commandments,
        the statutes, nor the ordinances which You commanded Your servant Moses. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Remember, I pray, the word that You commanded Your servant Moses,
        saying, \u2018If you are unfaithful, I will scatter you among the nations; "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "but if you return to Me, and keep My commandments and do them, though
        some of you were cast out to the farthest part of the heavens, yet I will
        gather them from there, and bring them to the place which I have chosen as
        a dwelling for My name.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Now these are Your servants and Your people, whom You have redeemed
        by Your great power, and by Your strong hand. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "O Lord, I pray, please let Your ear be attentive to the prayer of
        Your servant, and to the prayer of Your servants who desire to fear Your
        name; and let Your servant prosper this day, I pray, and grant him mercy
        in the sight of this man.\u201DFor I was the king\u2019s cupbearer."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Nehemiah Sent to Judah'
      title: Nehemiah Sent to Judah
      number: 1
      content: 'And it came to pass in the month of Nisan, in the twentieth year
        of King Artaxerxes, when wine was before him, that I took the wine and gave
        it to the king. Now I had never been sad in his presence before. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Therefore the king said to me, \u201CWhy is your face sad, since
        you are not sick? This is nothing but sorrow of heart.\u201DSo I became dreadfully
        afraid, "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "and said to the king, \u201CMay the king live forever! Why should
        my face not be sad, when the city, the place of my fathers\u2019 tombs, lies
        waste, and its gates are burned with fire?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Then the king said to me, \u201CWhat do you request?\u201DSo I prayed
        to the God of heaven. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "And I said to the king, \u201CIf it pleases the king, and if your
        servant has found favor in your sight, I ask that you send me to Judah, to
        the city of my fathers\u2019 tombs, that I may rebuild it.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Then the king said to me (the queen also sitting beside him), \u201CHow
        long will your journey be? And when will you return?\u201D So it pleased
        the king to send me; and I set him a time."
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Furthermore I said to the king, \u201CIf it pleases the king, let
        letters be given to me for the governors of  the  region beyond the River,
        that they must permit me to pass through till I come to Judah, "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "and a letter to Asaph the keeper of the king\u2019s forest, that
        he must give me timber to make beams for the gates of the citadel which pertains 
        to the temple, for the city wall, and for the house that I will occupy.\u201D
        And the king granted them to me according to the good hand of my God upon
        me."
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Then I went to the governors in  the  region beyond the River, and
        gave them the king\u2019s letters. Now the king had sent captains of the
        army and horsemen with me. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: Nehemiah Views the Wall of Jerusalem'
      title: Nehemiah Views the Wall of Jerusalem
      number: 10
      content: When Sanballat the Horonite and Tobiah the Ammonite official heard
        of  it, they were deeply disturbed that a man had come to seek the well-being
        of the children of Israel.
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'So I came to Jerusalem and was there three days. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Then I arose in the night, I and a few men with me; I told no one
        what my God had put in my heart to do at Jerusalem; nor was there any animal
        with me, except the one on which I rode. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'And I went out by night through the Valley Gate to the Serpent Well
        and the Refuse Gate, and viewed the walls of Jerusalem which were broken
        down and its gates which were burned with fire. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Then I went on to the Fountain Gate and to the King\u2019s Pool,
        but there  was no room for the animal under me to pass. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'So I went up in the night by the valley, and viewed the wall; then
        I turned back and entered by the Valley Gate, and so returned. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: And the officials did not know where I had gone or what I had done;
        I had not yet told the Jews, the priests, the nobles, the officials, or the
        others who did the work.
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Then I said to them, \u201CYou see the distress that we are in, how
        Jerusalem lies waste, and its gates are burned with fire. Come and let us
        build the wall of Jerusalem, that we may no longer be a reproach.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "And I told them of the hand of my God which had been good upon me,
        and also of the king\u2019s words that he had spoken to me.So they said,
        \u201CLet us rise up and build.\u201D Then they set their hands to this good
        work."
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "But when Sanballat the Horonite, Tobiah the Ammonite official, and
        Geshem the Arab heard of  it, they laughed at us and despised us, and said,
        \u201CWhat is this thing that you are doing? Will you rebel against the king?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "So I answered them, and said to them, \u201CThe God of heaven Himself
        will prosper us; therefore we His servants will arise and build, but you
        have no heritage or right or memorial in Jerusalem.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Rebuilding the Wall'
      title: Rebuilding the Wall
      number: 1
      content: 'Then Eliashib the high priest rose up with his brethren the priests
        and built the Sheep Gate; they consecrated it and hung its doors. They built
        as far as the Tower of the Hundred, and consecrated it, then as far as the
        Tower of Hananel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: Next to Eliashib  the men of Jericho built. And next to them Zaccur
        the son of Imri built.
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Also the sons of Hassenaah built the Fish Gate; they laid its beams
        and hung its doors with its bolts and bars. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And next to them Meremoth the son of Urijah, the son of Koz, made
        repairs. Next to them Meshullam the son of Berechiah, the son of Meshezabel,
        made repairs. Next to them Zadok the son of Baana made repairs. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: Next to them the Tekoites made repairs; but their nobles did not put
        their shoulders to the work of their Lord.
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Moreover Jehoiada the son of Paseah and Meshullam the son of Besodeiah
        repaired the Old Gate; they laid its beams and hung its doors, with its bolts
        and bars. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And next to them Melatiah the Gibeonite, Jadon the Meronothite, the
        men of Gibeon and Mizpah, repaired the residence of the governor of  the 
        region beyond the River. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Next to him Uzziel the son of Harhaiah, one of the goldsmiths, made
        repairs. Also next to him Hananiah, one of the perfumers, made repairs; and
        they fortified Jerusalem as far as the Broad Wall. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'And next to them Rephaiah the son of Hur, leader of half the district
        of Jerusalem, made repairs. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: Next to them Jedaiah the son of Harumaph made repairs in front of
        his house. And next to him Hattush the son of Hashabniah made repairs.
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Malchijah the son of Harim and Hashub the son of Pahath-Moab repaired
        another section, as well as the Tower of the Ovens. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: And next to him was Shallum the son of Hallohesh, leader of half the
        district of Jerusalem; he and his daughters made repairs.
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: Hanun and the inhabitants of Zanoah repaired the Valley Gate. They
        built it, hung its doors with its bolts and bars, and repaired a thousand
        cubits of the wall as far as the Refuse Gate.
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: Malchijah the son of Rechab, leader of the district of Beth Haccerem,
        repaired the Refuse Gate; he built it and hung its doors with its bolts and
        bars.
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Shallun the son of Col-Hozeh, leader of the district of Mizpah, repaired
        the Fountain Gate; he built it, covered it, hung its doors with its bolts
        and bars, and repaired the wall of the Pool of Shelah by the King\u2019s
        Garden, as far as the stairs that go down from the City of David. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: After him Nehemiah the son of Azbuk, leader of half the district of
        Beth Zur, made repairs as far as the  place in front of the tombs of David,
        to the man-made pool, and as far as the House of the Mighty.
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'After him the Levites, under Rehum the son of Bani, made repairs.
        Next to him Hashabiah, leader of half the district of Keilah, made repairs
        for his district. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'After him their brethren, under Bavai the son of Henadad, leader
        of the other half of the district of Keilah, made repairs. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'And next to him Ezer the son of Jeshua, the leader of Mizpah, repaired
        another section in front of the Ascent to the Armory at the buttress. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'After him Baruch the son of Zabbai carefully repaired the other section,
        from the buttress to the door of the house of Eliashib the high priest. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: After him Meremoth the son of Urijah, the son of Koz, repaired another
        section, from the door of the house of Eliashib to the end of the house of
        Eliashib.
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'And after him the priests, the men of the plain, made repairs. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'After him Benjamin and Hasshub made repairs opposite their house.
        After them Azariah the son of Maaseiah, the son of Ananiah, made repairs
        by his house. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'After him Binnui the son of Henadad repaired another section, from
        the house of Azariah to the buttress, even as far as the corner. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "Palal the son of Uzai made  repairs opposite the buttress, and on
        the tower which projects from the king\u2019s upper house that was by the
        court of the prison. After him Pedaiah the son of Parosh made  repairs."
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Moreover the Nethinim who dwelt in Ophel made  repairs as far as
        the  place in front of the Water Gate toward the east, and on the projecting
        tower. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: After them the Tekoites repaired another section, next to the great
        projecting tower, and as far as the wall of Ophel.
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'Beyond the Horse Gate the priests made repairs, each in front of
        his own house. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'After them Zadok the son of Immer made repairs in front of his own
        house. After him Shemaiah the son of Shechaniah, the keeper of the East Gate,
        made repairs. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'After him Hananiah the son of Shelemiah, and Hanun, the sixth son
        of Zalaph, repaired another section. After him Meshullam the son of Berechiah
        made repairs in front of his dwelling. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'After him Malchijah, one of the goldsmiths, made repairs as far as
        the house of the Nethinim and of the merchants, in front of the Miphkad Gate,
        and as far as the upper room at the corner. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: And between the upper room at the corner, as far as the Sheep Gate,
        the goldsmiths and the merchants made repairs.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Wall Defended Against Enemies'
      title: The Wall Defended Against Enemies
      number: 1
      content: 'But it so happened, when Sanballat heard that we were rebuilding
        the wall, that he was furious and very indignant, and mocked the Jews. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And he spoke before his brethren and the army of Samaria, and said,
        \u201CWhat are these feeble Jews doing? Will they fortify themselves? Will
        they offer sacrifices? Will they complete it in a day? Will they revive the
        stones from the heaps of rubbish\u2014stones that are burned?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Now Tobiah the Ammonite was beside him, and he said, \u201CWhatever
        they build, if even a fox goes up on  it, he will break down their stone
        wall.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Hear, O our God, for we are despised; turn their reproach on their
        own heads, and give them as plunder to a land of captivity! '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: Do not cover their iniquity, and do not let their sin be blotted out
        from before You; for they have provoked You to anger before the builders.
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: So we built the wall, and the entire wall was joined together up to
        half its height, for the people had a mind to work.
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Now it happened, when Sanballat, Tobiah, the Arabs, the Ammonites,
        and the Ashdodites heard that the walls of Jerusalem were being restored
        and the gaps were beginning to be closed, that they became very angry, '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'and all of them conspired together to come and attack Jerusalem and
        create confusion. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: Nevertheless we made our prayer to our God, and because of them we
        set a watch against them day and night.
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Then Judah said, \u201CThe strength of the laborers is failing, and
        there  is so much rubbish that we are not able to build the wall.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "And our adversaries said, \u201CThey will neither know nor see anything,
        till we come into their midst and kill them and cause the work to cease.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "So it was, when the Jews who dwelt near them came, that they told
        us ten times, \u201CFrom whatever place you turn, they  will  be upon us.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Therefore I positioned men behind the lower parts of the wall, at
        the openings; and I set the people according to their families, with their
        swords, their spears, and their bows. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "And I looked, and arose and said to the nobles, to the leaders, and
        to the rest of the people, \u201CDo not be afraid of them. Remember the Lord,
        great and awesome, and fight for your brethren, your sons, your daughters,
        your wives, and your houses.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'And it happened, when our enemies heard that it was known to us,
        and that God had brought their plot to nothing, that all of us returned to
        the wall, everyone to his work. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'So it was, from that time on, that half of my servants worked at
        construction, while the other half held the spears, the shields, the bows,
        and wore armor; and the leaders were behind all the house of Judah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Those who built on the wall, and those who carried burdens, loaded
        themselves so that with one hand they worked at construction, and with the
        other held a weapon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: Every one of the builders had his sword girded at his side as he built.
        And the one who sounded the trumpet was beside me.
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Then I said to the nobles, the rulers, and the rest of the people,
        \u201CThe work is great and extensive, and we are separated far from one
        another on the wall. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Wherever you hear the sound of the trumpet, rally to us there. Our
        God will fight for us.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'So we labored in the work, and half of the  men held the spears from
        daybreak until the stars appeared. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "At the same time I also said to the people, \u201CLet each man and
        his servant stay at night in Jerusalem, that they may be our guard by night
        and a working party by day.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: So neither I, my brethren, my servants, nor the men of the guard who
        followed me took off our clothes, except that everyone took them off for
        washing.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Nehemiah Deals with Oppression'
      title: Nehemiah Deals with Oppression
      number: 1
      content: 'And there was a great outcry of the people and their wives against
        their Jewish brethren. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "For there were those who said, \u201CWe, our sons, and our daughters
        are many; therefore let us get grain, that we may eat and live.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "There were also some who said, \u201CWe have mortgaged our lands
        and vineyards and houses, that we might buy grain because of the famine.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "There were also those who said, \u201CWe have borrowed money for
        the king\u2019s tax on our lands and vineyards. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Yet now our flesh is as the flesh of our brethren, our children as
        their children; and indeed we are forcing our sons and our daughters to be
        slaves, and some of our daughters have been brought into slavery. It  is
        not in our power to  redeem  them, for other men have our lands and vineyards.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And I became very angry when I heard their outcry and these words. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "After serious thought, I rebuked the nobles and rulers, and said
        to them, \u201CEach of you is exacting usury from his brother.\u201D So I
        called a great assembly against them. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "And I said to them, \u201CAccording to our ability we have redeemed
        our Jewish brethren who were sold to the nations. Now indeed, will you even
        sell your brethren? Or should they be sold to us?\u201DThen they were silenced
        and found nothing to  say.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Then I said, \u201CWhat you are doing is not good. Should you not
        walk in the fear of our God because of the reproach of the nations, our enemies? "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'I also, with my brethren and my servants, am lending them money and
        grain. Please, let us stop this usury! '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Restore now to them, even this day, their lands, their vineyards,
        their olive groves, and their houses, also a hundredth of the money and the
        grain, the new wine and the oil, that you have charged them.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "So they said, \u201CWe will restore it, and will require nothing
        from them; we will do as you say.\u201DThen I called the priests, and required
        an oath from them that they would do according to this promise. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: The Generosity of Nehemiah'
      title: The Generosity of Nehemiah
      number: 13
      content: "Then I shook out the fold of my garment and said, \u201CSo may God
        shake out each man from his house, and from his property, who does not perform
        this promise. Even thus may he be shaken out and emptied.\u201DAnd all the
        assembly said, \u201CAmen!\u201D and praised the Lord. Then the people did
        according to this promise."
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Moreover, from the time that I was appointed to be their governor
        in the land of Judah, from the twentieth year until the thirty-second year
        of King Artaxerxes, twelve years, neither I nor my brothers ate the governor\u2019s
        provisions. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'But the former governors who were before me laid burdens on the people,
        and took from them bread and wine, besides forty shekels of silver. Yes,
        even their servants bore rule over the people, but I did not do so, because
        of the fear of God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: Indeed, I also continued the work on this wall, and we did not buy
        any land. All my servants were gathered there for the work.
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'And at my table were one hundred and fifty Jews and rulers, besides
        those who came to us from the nations around us. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Now that  which was prepared daily was one ox and six choice sheep.
        Also fowl were prepared for me, and once every ten days an abundance of all
        kinds of wine. Yet in spite of this I did not demand the governor\u2019s
        provisions, because the bondage was heavy on this people."
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: Remember me, my God, for good, according  to all that I have done
        for this people.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Conspiracy Against Nehemiah'
      title: Conspiracy Against Nehemiah
      number: 1
      content: 'Now it happened when Sanballat, Tobiah, Geshem the Arab, and the
        rest of our enemies heard that I had rebuilt the wall, and that there were
        no breaks left in it (though at that time I had not hung the doors in the
        gates), '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "that Sanballat and Geshem sent to me, saying, \u201CCome, let us
        meet together among the villages in the plain of Ono.\u201D But they thought
        to do me harm."
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "So I sent messengers to them, saying, \u201CI am doing a great work,
        so that I cannot come down. Why should the work cease while I leave it and
        go down to you?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: But they sent me this message four times, and I answered them in the
        same manner.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Then Sanballat sent his servant to me as before, the fifth time,
        with an open letter in his hand. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'In it was written:It is reported among the nations, and Geshem says,
        that you and the Jews plan to rebel; therefore, according to these rumors,
        you are rebuilding the wall, that you may be their king. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "And you have also appointed prophets to proclaim concerning you at
        Jerusalem, saying, \u201CThere  is a king in Judah!\u201D Now these matters
        will be reported to the king. So come, therefore, and let us consult together."
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Then I sent to him, saying, \u201CNo such things as you say are being
        done, but you invent them in your own heart.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "For they all were  trying  to make us afraid, saying, \u201CTheir
        hands will be weakened in the work, and it will not be done.\u201DNow therefore,
        O  God, strengthen my hands."
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Afterward I came to the house of Shemaiah the son of Delaiah, the
        son of Mehetabel, who was a secret informer; and he said, \u201CLet us meet
        together in the house of God, within the temple, and let us close the doors
        of the temple, for they are coming to kill you; indeed, at night they will
        come to kill you.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "And I said, \u201CShould such a man as I flee? And who is  there
        such as I who would go into the temple to save his life? I will not go in!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Then I perceived that God had not sent him at all, but that he pronounced
        this prophecy against me because Tobiah and Sanballat had hired him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: For this reason he was hired, that I should be afraid and act that
        way and sin, so that they might have cause for an evil report, that they
        might reproach me.
      comments: []
    - name: '14: The Wall Completed'
      title: The Wall Completed
      number: 14
      content: My God, remember Tobiah and Sanballat, according to these their works,
        and the prophetess Noadiah and the rest of the prophets who would have made
        me afraid.
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'So the wall was finished on the twenty-fifth day of Elul, in fifty-two
        days. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: And it happened, when all our enemies heard of  it, and all the nations
        around us saw these  things, that they were very disheartened in their own
        eyes; for they perceived that this work was done by our God.
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Also in those days the nobles of Judah sent many letters to Tobiah,
        and the  letters  of Tobiah came to them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'For many in Judah were pledged to him, because he was the son-in-law
        of Shechaniah the son of Arah, and his son Jehohanan had married the daughter
        of Meshullam the son of Berechiah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: Also they reported his good deeds before me, and reported my words
        to him. Tobiah sent letters to frighten me.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: 'Then it was, when the wall was built and I had hung the doors, when
        the gatekeepers, the singers, and the Levites had been appointed, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: that I gave the charge of Jerusalem to my brother Hanani, and Hananiah
        the leader of the citadel, for he was a faithful man and feared God more
        than many.
      comments: []
    - name: '3: The Captives Who Returned to Jerusalem'
      title: The Captives Who Returned to Jerusalem
      number: 3
      content: "And I said to them, \u201CDo not let the gates of Jerusalem be opened
        until the sun is hot; and while they stand guard, let them shut and bar the
        doors; and appoint guards from among the inhabitants of Jerusalem, one at
        his watch station and another in front of his own house.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Now the city was large and spacious, but the people in it were  few,
        and the houses were not rebuilt. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Then my God put it into my heart to gather the nobles, the rulers,
        and the people, that they might be registered by genealogy. And I found a
        register of the genealogy of those who had come up in the first return, and
        found written in it:'
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: These are the people of the province who came back from the captivity,
        of those who had been carried away, whom Nebuchadnezzar the king of Babylon
        had carried away, and who returned to Jerusalem and Judah, everyone to his
        city.
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Those who came with Zerubbabel were Jeshua, Nehemiah, Azariah, Raamiah,
        Nahamani, Mordecai, Bilshan, Mispereth, Bigvai, Nehum, and Baanah.The number
        of the men of the people of Israel: '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: the sons of Parosh, two thousand one hundred and seventy-two;
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: the sons of Shephatiah, three hundred and seventy-two;
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: the sons of Arah, six hundred and fifty-two;
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: the sons of Pahath-Moab, of the sons of Jeshua and Joab, two thousand
        eight hundred and eighteen;
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: the sons of Elam, one thousand two hundred and fifty-four;
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: the sons of Zattu, eight hundred and forty-five;
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: the sons of Zaccai, seven hundred and sixty;
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: the sons of Binnui, six hundred and forty-eight;
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: the sons of Bebai, six hundred and twenty-eight;
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: the sons of Azgad, two thousand three hundred and twenty-two;
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: the sons of Adonikam, six hundred and sixty-seven;
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: the sons of Bigvai, two thousand and sixty-seven;
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: the sons of Adin, six hundred and fifty-five;
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: the sons of Ater of Hezekiah, ninety-eight;
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: the sons of Hashum, three hundred and twenty-eight;
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: the sons of Bezai, three hundred and twenty-four;
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: the sons of Hariph, one hundred and twelve;
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: the sons of Gibeon, ninety-five;
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: the men of Bethlehem and Netophah, one hundred and eighty-eight;
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: the men of Anathoth, one hundred and twenty-eight;
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: the men of Beth Azmaveth, forty-two;
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: the men of Kirjath Jearim, Chephirah, and Beeroth, seven hundred and
        forty-three;
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: the men of Ramah and Geba, six hundred and twenty-one;
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: the men of Michmas, one hundred and twenty-two;
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: the men of Bethel and Ai, one hundred and twenty-three;
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: the men of the other Nebo, fifty-two;
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: the sons of the other Elam, one thousand two hundred and fifty-four;
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: the sons of Harim, three hundred and twenty;
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: the sons of Jericho, three hundred and forty-five;
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: the sons of Lod, Hadid, and Ono, seven hundred and twenty-one;
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: the sons of Senaah, three thousand nine hundred and thirty.
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'The priests: the sons of Jedaiah, of the house of Jeshua, nine hundred
        and seventy-three;'
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: the sons of Immer, one thousand and fifty-two;
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: the sons of Pashhur, one thousand two hundred and forty-seven;
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: the sons of Harim, one thousand and seventeen.
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: 'The Levites: the sons of Jeshua, of Kadmiel,and of the sons of Hodevah,
        seventy-four.'
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: 'The singers: the sons of Asaph, one hundred and forty-eight.'
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: 'The gatekeepers: the sons of Shallum,the sons of Ater,the sons of
        Talmon,the sons of Akkub,the sons of Hatita,the sons of Shobai, one hundred
        and thirty-eight.'
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: 'The Nethinim: the sons of Ziha,the sons of Hasupha,the sons of Tabbaoth,'
      comments: []
    - name: '47: '
      title: 
      number: 47
      content: the sons of Keros,the sons of Sia,the sons of Padon,
      comments: []
    - name: '48: '
      title: 
      number: 48
      content: the sons of Lebana,the sons of Hagaba,the sons of Salmai,
      comments: []
    - name: '49: '
      title: 
      number: 49
      content: the sons of Hanan,the sons of Giddel,the sons of Gahar,
      comments: []
    - name: '50: '
      title: 
      number: 50
      content: the sons of Reaiah,the sons of Rezin,the sons of Nekoda,
      comments: []
    - name: '51: '
      title: 
      number: 51
      content: the sons of Gazzam,the sons of Uzza,the sons of Paseah,
      comments: []
    - name: '52: '
      title: 
      number: 52
      content: the sons of Besai,the sons of Meunim,the sons of Nephishesim,
      comments: []
    - name: '53: '
      title: 
      number: 53
      content: the sons of Bakbuk,the sons of Hakupha,the sons of Harhur,
      comments: []
    - name: '54: '
      title: 
      number: 54
      content: the sons of Bazlith,the sons of Mehida,the sons of Harsha,
      comments: []
    - name: '55: '
      title: 
      number: 55
      content: the sons of Barkos,the sons of Sisera,the sons of Tamah,
      comments: []
    - name: '56: '
      title: 
      number: 56
      content: the sons of Neziah,and the sons of Hatipha.
      comments: []
    - name: '57: '
      title: 
      number: 57
      content: "The sons of Solomon\u2019s servants: the sons of Sotai,the sons of
        Sophereth,the sons of Perida,"
      comments: []
    - name: '58: '
      title: 
      number: 58
      content: the sons of Jaala,the sons of Darkon,the sons of Giddel,
      comments: []
    - name: '59: '
      title: 
      number: 59
      content: the sons of Shephatiah,the sons of Hattil,the sons of Pochereth of
        Zebaim,and the sons of Amon.
      comments: []
    - name: '60: '
      title: 
      number: 60
      content: "All the Nethinim, and the sons of Solomon\u2019s servants, were three
        hundred and ninety-two."
      comments: []
    - name: '61: '
      title: 
      number: 61
      content: "And these were the ones who came up from Tel Melah, Tel Harsha, Cherub,
        Addon, and Immer, but they could not identify their father\u2019s house nor
        their lineage, whether they were of Israel: "
      comments: []
    - name: '62: '
      title: 
      number: 62
      content: the sons of Delaiah,the sons of Tobiah,the sons of Nekoda, six hundred
        and forty-two;
      comments: []
    - name: '63: '
      title: 
      number: 63
      content: 'and of the priests: the sons of Habaiah,the sons of Koz,the sons
        of Barzillai, who took a wife of the daughters of Barzillai the Gileadite,
        and was called by their name.'
      comments: []
    - name: '64: '
      title: 
      number: 64
      content: 'These sought their listing among those who were registered by genealogy,
        but it was not found; therefore they were excluded from the priesthood as
        defiled. '
      comments: []
    - name: '65: '
      title: 
      number: 65
      content: And the governor said to them that they should not eat of the most
        holy things till a priest could consult with the Urim and Thummim.
      comments: []
    - name: '66: '
      title: 
      number: 66
      content: 'Altogether the whole assembly was forty-two thousand three hundred
        and sixty, '
      comments: []
    - name: '67: '
      title: 
      number: 67
      content: 'besides their male and female servants, of whom there  were seven
        thousand three hundred and thirty-seven; and they had two hundred and forty-five
        men and women singers. '
      comments: []
    - name: '68: '
      title: 
      number: 68
      content: 'Their horses were seven hundred and thirty-six, their mules two hundred
        and forty-five, '
      comments: []
    - name: '69: '
      title: 
      number: 69
      content: their camels four hundred and thirty-five, and donkeys six thousand
        seven hundred and twenty.
      comments: []
    - name: '70: '
      title: 
      number: 70
      content: "And some of the heads of the fathers\u2019 houses gave to the work.
        The governor gave to the treasury one thousand gold drachmas, fifty basins,
        and five hundred and thirty priestly garments. "
      comments: []
    - name: '71: '
      title: 
      number: 71
      content: "Some of the heads of the fathers\u2019 houses gave to the treasury
        of the work twenty thousand gold drachmas, and two thousand two hundred silver
        minas. "
      comments: []
    - name: '72: '
      title: 
      number: 72
      content: And that which the rest of the people gave was twenty thousand gold
        drachmas, two thousand silver minas, and sixty-seven priestly garments.
      comments: []
    - name: '73: Ezra Reads the Law'
      title: Ezra Reads the Law
      number: 73
      content: So the priests, the Levites, the gatekeepers, the singers, some of
        the people, the Nethinim, and all Israel dwelt in their cities.When the seventh
        month came, the children of Israel were in their cities.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: 'Now all the people gathered together as one man in the open square
        that was  in front of the Water Gate; and they told Ezra the scribe to bring
        the Book of the Law of Moses, which the Lord had commanded Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'So Ezra the priest brought the Law before the assembly of men and
        women and all who could hear with understanding on the first day of the seventh
        month. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: Then he read from it in the open square that was in front of the Water
        Gate from morning until midday, before the men and women and those who could
        understand; and the ears of all the people were  attentive to the Book of
        the Law.
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'So Ezra the scribe stood on a platform of wood which they had made
        for the purpose; and beside him, at his right hand, stood Mattithiah, Shema,
        Anaiah, Urijah, Hilkiah, and Maaseiah; and at his left hand Pedaiah, Mishael,
        Malchijah, Hashum, Hashbadana, Zechariah, and Meshullam. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And Ezra opened the book in the sight of all the people, for he was
        standing above all the people; and when he opened it, all the people stood
        up. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "And Ezra blessed the Lord, the great God.Then all the people answered,
        \u201CAmen, Amen!\u201D while lifting up their hands. And they bowed their
        heads and worshiped the Lord with their faces to the ground."
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Also Jeshua, Bani, Sherebiah, Jamin, Akkub, Shabbethai, Hodijah,
        Maaseiah, Kelita, Azariah, Jozabad, Hanan, Pelaiah, and the Levites, helped
        the people to understand the Law; and the people stood in their place. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: So they read distinctly from the book, in the Law of God; and they
        gave the sense, and helped them to understand the reading.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "And Nehemiah, who was the governor, Ezra the priest and scribe, and
        the Levites who taught the people said to all the people, \u201CThis day
        is holy to the Lord your God; do not mourn nor weep.\u201D For all the people
        wept, when they heard the words of the Law."
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Then he said to them, \u201CGo your way, eat the fat, drink the sweet,
        and send portions to those for whom nothing is prepared; for this day is
        holy to our Lord. Do not sorrow, for the joy of the Lord is your strength.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "So the Levites quieted all the people, saying, \u201CBe still, for
        the day is holy; do not be grieved.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: The Feast of Tabernacles'
      title: The Feast of Tabernacles
      number: 12
      content: And all the people went their way to eat and drink, to send portions
        and rejoice greatly, because they understood the words that were declared
        to them.
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Now on the second day the heads of the fathers\u2019 houses of all
        the people, with the priests and Levites, were gathered to Ezra the scribe,
        in order to understand the words of the Law. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'And they found written in the Law, which the Lord had commanded by
        Moses, that the children of Israel should dwell in booths during the feast
        of the seventh month, '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "and that they should announce and proclaim in all their cities and
        in Jerusalem, saying, \u201CGo out to the mountain, and bring olive branches,
        branches of oil trees, myrtle branches, palm branches, and branches of leafy
        trees, to make booths, as it  is written.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Then the people went out and brought them and made themselves booths,
        each one on the roof of his house, or in their courtyards or the courts of
        the house of God, and in the open square of the Water Gate and in the open
        square of the Gate of Ephraim. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'So the whole assembly of those who had returned from the captivity
        made booths and sat under the booths; for since the days of Joshua the son
        of Nun until that day the children of Israel had not done so. And there was
        very great gladness. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: Also day by day, from the first day until the last day, he read from
        the Book of the Law of God. And they kept the feast seven days; and on the
        eighth day there  was a sacred assembly, according to the prescribed manner.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The People Confess Their Sins'
      title: The People Confess Their Sins
      number: 1
      content: 'Now on the twenty-fourth day of this month the children of Israel
        were assembled with fasting, in sackcloth, and with dust on their heads. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Then those of Israelite lineage separated themselves from all foreigners;
        and they stood and confessed their sins and the iniquities of their fathers. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "And they stood up in their place and read from the Book of the Law
        of the Lord their God for  one\u2013fourth of the day; and for  another fourth
        they confessed and worshiped the Lord their God."
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Then Jeshua, Bani, Kadmiel, Shebaniah, Bunni, Sherebiah, Bani, and
        Chenani stood on the stairs of the Levites and cried out with a loud voice
        to the Lord their God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "And the Levites, Jeshua, Kadmiel, Bani, Hashabniah, Sherebiah, Hodijah,
        Shebaniah, and Pethahiah, said:\u201CStand up and bless the Lord your GodForever
        and ever!\u201CBlessed be Your glorious name,Which is exalted above all blessing
        and praise!"
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: You alone are the Lord;You have made heaven,The heaven of heavens,
        with all their host,The earth and everything on it,The seas and all that
        is in them,And You preserve them all.The host of heaven worships You.
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "\u201CYou are the Lord God,Who chose Abram,And brought him out of
        Ur of the Chaldeans,And gave him the name Abraham;"
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "You found his heart faithful before You,And made a covenant with
        himTo give the land of the Canaanites,The Hittites, the Amorites,The Perizzites,
        the Jebusites,And the Girgashites\u2014To give it to his descendants.You
        have performed Your words,For You are righteous."
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "\u201CYou saw the affliction of our fathers in Egypt,And heard their
        cry by the Red Sea."
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: You showed signs and wonders against Pharaoh,Against all his servants,And
        against all the people of his land.For You knew that they acted proudly against
        them.So You made a name for Yourself, as it  is this day.
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: And You divided the sea before them,So that they went through the
        midst of the sea on the dry land;And their persecutors You threw into the
        deep,As a stone into the mighty waters.
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: Moreover You led them by day with a cloudy pillar,And by night with
        a pillar of fire,To give them light on the roadWhich they should travel.
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "\u201CYou came down also on Mount Sinai,And spoke with them from
        heaven,And gave them just ordinances and true laws,Good statutes and commandments."
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: You made known to them Your holy Sabbath,And commanded them precepts,
        statutes and laws,By the hand of Moses Your servant.
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: You gave them bread from heaven for their hunger,And brought them
        water out of the rock for their thirst,And told them to go in to possess
        the landWhich You had sworn to give them.
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "\u201CBut they and our fathers acted proudly,Hardened their necks,And
        did not heed Your commandments."
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: They refused to obey,And they were not mindful of Your wondersThat
        You did among them.But they hardened their necks,And in their rebellionThey
        appointed a leaderTo return to their bondage.But You are God,Ready to pardon,Gracious
        and merciful,Slow to anger,Abundant in kindness,And did not forsake them.
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "\u201CEven when they made a molded calf for themselves,And said,
        \u2018This is your godThat brought you up out of Egypt,\u2019And worked great
        provocations,"
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: Yet in Your manifold merciesYou did not forsake them in the wilderness.The
        pillar of the cloud did not depart from them by day,To lead them on the road;Nor
        the pillar of fire by night,To show them light,And the way they should go.
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: You also gave Your good Spirit to instruct them,And did not withhold
        Your manna from their mouth,And gave them water for their thirst.
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: Forty years You sustained them in the wilderness;They lacked nothing;Their
        clothes did not wear outAnd their feet did not swell.
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "\u201CMoreover You gave them kingdoms and nations,And divided them
        into districts.So they took possession of the land of Sihon,The land of the
        king of Heshbon,And the land of Og king of Bashan."
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: You also multiplied their children as the stars of heaven,And brought
        them into the landWhich You had told their fathersTo go in and possess.
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: So the people went inAnd possessed the land;You subdued before them
        the inhabitants of the land,The Canaanites,And gave them into their hands,With
        their kingsAnd the people of the land,That they might do with them as they
        wished.
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: And they took strong cities and a rich land,And possessed houses full
        of all goods,Cisterns already dug, vineyards, olive groves,And fruit trees
        in abundance.So they ate and were filled and grew fat,And delighted themselves
        in Your great goodness.
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "\u201CNevertheless they were disobedientAnd rebelled against You,Cast
        Your law behind their backsAnd killed Your prophets, who testified against
        themTo turn them to Yourself;And they worked great provocations."
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: Therefore You delivered them into the hand of their enemies,Who oppressed
        them;And in the time of their trouble,When they cried to You,You heard from
        heaven;And according to Your abundant merciesYou gave them deliverers who
        saved themFrom the hand of their enemies.
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "\u201CBut after they had rest,They again did evil before You.Therefore
        You left them in the hand of their enemies,So that they had dominion over
        them;Yet when they returned and cried out to You,You heard from heaven;And
        many times You delivered them according to Your mercies,"
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "And testified against them,That You might bring them back to Your
        law.Yet they acted proudly,And did not heed Your commandments,But sinned
        against Your judgments,\u2018Which if a man does, he shall live by them.\u2019And
        they shrugged their shoulders,Stiffened their necks,And would not hear."
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: Yet for many years You had patience with them,And testified against
        them by Your Spirit in Your prophets.Yet they would not listen;Therefore
        You gave them into the hand of the peoples of the lands.
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: Nevertheless in Your great mercyYou did not utterly consume them nor
        forsake them;For You are God, gracious and merciful.
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "\u201CNow therefore, our God,The great, the mighty, and awesome God,Who
        keeps covenant and mercy:Do not let all the trouble seem small before YouThat
        has come upon us,Our kings and our princes,Our priests and our prophets,Our
        fathers and on all Your people,From the days of the kings of Assyria until
        this day."
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: However You are just in all that has befallen us;For You have dealt
        faithfully,But we have done wickedly.
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: Neither our kings nor our princes,Our priests nor our fathers,Have
        kept Your law,Nor heeded Your commandments and Your testimonies,With which
        You testified against them.
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: For they have not served You in their kingdom,Or in the many good
        things that You gave them,Or in the large and rich land which You set before
        them;Nor did they turn from their wicked works.
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "\u201CHere we are, servants today!And the land that You gave to our
        fathers,To eat its fruit and its bounty,Here we are, servants in it!"
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: And it yields much increase to the kingsYou have set over us,Because
        of our sins;Also they have dominion over our bodies and our cattleAt their
        pleasure;And we are in great distress.
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: "\u201CAnd because of all this,We make a sure covenant and write it;Our
        leaders, our Levites, and our priests seal it.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The People Who Sealed the Covenant'
      title: The People Who Sealed the Covenant
      number: 1
      content: 'Now those who placed their seal on the  document  were:Nehemiah the
        governor, the son of Hacaliah, and Zedekiah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Seraiah, Azariah, Jeremiah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Pashhur, Amariah, Malchijah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Hattush, Shebaniah, Malluch, '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Harim, Meremoth, Obadiah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Daniel, Ginnethon, Baruch, '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Meshullam, Abijah, Mijamin, '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: Maaziah, Bilgai, and Shemaiah. These were the priests.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'The Levites: Jeshua the son of Azaniah, Binnui of the sons of Henadad,
        and Kadmiel.'
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Their brethren: Shebaniah, Hodijah, Kelita, Pelaiah, Hanan, '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Micha, Rehob, Hashabiah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Zaccur, Sherebiah, Shebaniah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: Hodijah, Bani, and Beninu.
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'The leaders of the people: Parosh, Pahath-Moab, Elam, Zattu, Bani, '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Bunni, Azgad, Bebai, '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Adonijah, Bigvai, Adin, '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Ater, Hezekiah, Azzur, '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Hodijah, Hashum, Bezai, '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Hariph, Anathoth, Nebai, '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Magpiash, Meshullam, Hezir, '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Meshezabel, Zadok, Jaddua, '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Pelatiah, Hanan, Anaiah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Hoshea, Hananiah, Hasshub, '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Hallohesh, Pilha, Shobek, '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Rehum, Hashabnah, Maaseiah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Ahijah, Hanan, Anan, '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: The Covenant That Was Sealed'
      title: The Covenant That Was Sealed
      number: 27
      content: Malluch, Harim, and Baanah.
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "Now the rest of the people\u2014the priests, the Levites, the gatekeepers,
        the singers, the Nethinim, and all those who had separated themselves from
        the peoples of the lands to the Law of God, their wives, their sons, and
        their daughters, everyone who had knowledge and understanding\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "these joined with their brethren, their nobles, and entered into
        a curse and an oath to walk in God\u2019s Law, which was given by Moses the
        servant of God, and to observe and do all the commandments of the Lord our
        Lord, and His ordinances and His statutes: "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'We would not give our daughters as wives to the peoples of the land,
        nor take their daughters for our sons; '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "if the peoples of the land brought wares or any grain to sell on
        the Sabbath day, we would not buy it from them on the Sabbath, or on a holy
        day; and we would forego the seventh year\u2019s produce and the exacting
        of every debt."
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'Also we made ordinances for ourselves, to exact from ourselves yearly
        one-third of a shekel for the service of the house of our God: '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'for the showbread, for the regular grain offering, for the regular
        burnt offering of the Sabbaths, the New Moons, and the set feasts; for the
        holy things, for the sin offerings to make atonement for Israel, and all
        the work of the house of our God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "We cast lots among the priests, the Levites, and the people, for
        bringing the wood offering into the house of our God, according to our fathers\u2019
        houses, at the appointed times year by year, to burn on the altar of the
        Lord our God as it  is written in the Law."
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'And we  made  ordinances  to bring the firstfruits of our ground
        and the firstfruits of all fruit of all trees, year by year, to the house
        of the Lord; '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'to bring the firstborn of our sons and our cattle, as it  is written
        in the Law, and the firstborn of our herds and our flocks, to the house of
        our God, to the priests who minister in the house of our God; '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'to bring the firstfruits of our dough, our offerings, the fruit from
        all kinds of trees, the new wine and oil, to the priests, to the storerooms
        of the house of our God; and to bring the tithes of our land to the Levites,
        for the Levites should receive the tithes in all our farming communities. '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: And the priest, the descendant of Aaron, shall be with the Levites
        when the Levites receive tithes; and the Levites shall bring up a tenth of
        the tithes to the house of our God, to the rooms of the storehouse.
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: For the children of Israel and the children of Levi shall bring the
        offering of the grain, of the new wine and the oil, to the storerooms where
        the articles of the sanctuary are, where the priests who minister and the
        gatekeepers and the singers are; and we will not neglect the house of our
        God.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The People Dwelling in Jerusalem'
      title: The People Dwelling in Jerusalem
      number: 1
      content: 'Now the leaders of the people dwelt at Jerusalem; the rest of the
        people cast lots to bring one out of ten to dwell in Jerusalem, the holy
        city, and nine-tenths were  to  dwell in other cities. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: And the people blessed all the men who willingly offered themselves
        to dwell at Jerusalem.
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "These are the heads of the province who dwelt in Jerusalem. (But
        in the cities of Judah everyone dwelt in his own possession in their cities\u2014Israelites,
        priests, Levites, Nethinim, and descendants of Solomon\u2019s servants.) "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Also in Jerusalem dwelt some of the children of Judah and of the
        children of Benjamin.The children of Judah: Athaiah the son of Uzziah, the
        son of Zechariah, the son of Amariah, the son of Shephatiah, the son of Mahalalel,
        of the children of Perez; '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'and Maaseiah the son of Baruch, the son of Col-Hozeh, the son of
        Hazaiah, the son of Adaiah, the son of Joiarib, the son of Zechariah, the
        son of Shiloni. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: All the sons of Perez who dwelt at Jerusalem were four hundred and
        sixty-eight valiant men.
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And these are the sons of Benjamin: Sallu the son of Meshullam, the
        son of Joed, the son of Pedaiah, the son of Kolaiah, the son of Maaseiah,
        the son of Ithiel, the son of Jeshaiah; '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'and after him Gabbai and Sallai, nine hundred and twenty-eight. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: Joel the son of Zichri was their overseer, and Judah the son of Senuah
        was second over the city.
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Of the priests: Jedaiah the son of Joiarib, and Jachin; '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Seraiah the son of Hilkiah, the son of Meshullam, the son of Zadok,
        the son of Meraioth, the son of Ahitub, was the leader of the house of God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Their brethren who did the work of the house were eight hundred and
        twenty-two; and Adaiah the son of Jeroham, the son of Pelaliah, the son of
        Amzi, the son of Zechariah, the son of Pashhur, the son of Malchijah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "and his brethren, heads of the fathers\u2019 houses, were two hundred
        and forty-two; and Amashai the son of Azarel, the son of Ahzai, the son of
        Meshillemoth, the son of Immer, "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: and their brethren, mighty men of valor, were one hundred and twenty-eight.
        Their overseer was Zabdiel the son of one  of the great men.
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Also of the Levites: Shemaiah the son of Hasshub, the son of Azrikam,
        the son of Hashabiah, the son of Bunni; '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Shabbethai and Jozabad, of the heads of the Levites, had the oversight
        of the business outside of the house of God; '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Mattaniah the son of Micha, the son of Zabdi, the son of Asaph, the
        leader who began the thanksgiving with prayer; Bakbukiah, the second among
        his brethren; and Abda the son of Shammua, the son of Galal, the son of Jeduthun. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: All the Levites in the holy city were two hundred and eighty-four.
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: Moreover the gatekeepers, Akkub, Talmon, and their brethren who kept
        the gates, were one hundred and seventy-two.
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'And the rest of Israel, of the priests and Levites, were in all the
        cities of Judah, everyone in his inheritance. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: But the Nethinim dwelt in Ophel. And Ziha and Gishpa were over the
        Nethinim.
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Also the overseer of the Levites at Jerusalem was Uzzi the son of
        Bani, the son of Hashabiah, the son of Mattaniah, the son of Micha, of the
        sons of Asaph, the singers in charge of the service of the house of God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "For it  was the king\u2019s command concerning them that a certain
        portion should be for the singers, a quota day by day. "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: The People Dwelling Outside Jerusalem'
      title: The People Dwelling Outside Jerusalem
      number: 24
      content: "Pethahiah the son of Meshezabel, of the children of Zerah the son
        of Judah, was  the king\u2019s deputy in all matters concerning the people."
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'And as for the villages with their fields, some of the children of
        Judah dwelt in Kirjath Arba and its villages, Dibon and its villages, Jekabzeel
        and its villages; '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'in Jeshua, Moladah, Beth Pelet, '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'Hazar Shual, and Beersheba and its villages; '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'in Ziklag and Meconah and its villages; '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'in En Rimmon, Zorah, Jarmuth, '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: Zanoah, Adullam, and their villages; in Lachish and its fields; in
        Azekah and its villages. They dwelt from Beersheba to the Valley of Hinnom.
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'Also the children of Benjamin from Geba dwelt in Michmash, Aija,
        and Bethel, and their villages; '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'in Anathoth, Nob, Ananiah; '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'in Hazor, Ramah, Gittaim; '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'in Hadid, Zeboim, Neballat; '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'in Lod, Ono, and  the Valley of Craftsmen. '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: Some of the Judean divisions of Levites were in Benjamin.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Priests and Levites'
      title: The Priests and Levites
      number: 1
      content: 'Now these are the priests and the Levites who came up with Zerubbabel
        the son of Shealtiel, and Jeshua: Seraiah, Jeremiah, Ezra, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Amariah, Malluch, Hattush, '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Shechaniah, Rehum, Meremoth, '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Iddo, Ginnethoi, Abijah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Mijamin, Maadiah, Bilgah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Shemaiah, Joiarib, Jedaiah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: Sallu, Amok, Hilkiah, and Jedaiah.These were the heads of the priests
        and their brethren in the days of Jeshua.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Moreover the Levites were Jeshua, Binnui, Kadmiel, Sherebiah, Judah,
        and Mattaniah who  led the thanksgiving psalms, he and his brethren. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: Also Bakbukiah and Unni, their brethren, stood across from them in
        their duties.
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Jeshua begot Joiakim, Joiakim begot Eliashib, Eliashib begot Joiada, '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: Joiada begot Jonathan, and Jonathan begot Jaddua.
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Now in the days of Joiakim, the priests, the heads of the fathers\u2019
        houses  were: of Seraiah, Meraiah; of Jeremiah, Hananiah; "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'of Ezra, Meshullam; of Amariah, Jehohanan; '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'of Melichu, Jonathan; of Shebaniah, Joseph; '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'of Harim, Adna; of Meraioth, Helkai; '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'of Iddo, Zechariah; of Ginnethon, Meshullam; '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'of Abijah, Zichri; the  son of Minjamin; of Moadiah, Piltai; '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'of Bilgah, Shammua; of Shemaiah, Jehonathan; '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'of Joiarib, Mattenai; of Jedaiah, Uzzi; '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'of Sallai, Kallai; of Amok, Eber; '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: of Hilkiah, Hashabiah; and of Jedaiah, Nethanel.
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "During the reign of Darius the Persian, a record was  also  kept
        of the Levites and priests who  had  been  heads of their fathers\u2019 houses
        in the days of Eliashib, Joiada, Johanan, and Jaddua. "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "The sons of Levi, the heads of the fathers\u2019 houses until the
        days of Johanan the son of Eliashib, were written in the book of the chronicles."
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'And the heads of the Levites were Hashabiah, Sherebiah, and Jeshua
        the son of Kadmiel, with their brothers across from them, to praise and give
        thanks, group alternating with group, according to the command of David the
        man of God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Mattaniah, Bakbukiah, Obadiah, Meshullam, Talmon, and Akkub were
        gatekeepers keeping the watch at the storerooms of the gates. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: Nehemiah Dedicates the Wall'
      title: Nehemiah Dedicates the Wall
      number: 26
      content: These lived in the days of Joiakim the son of Jeshua, the son of Jozadak,
        and in the days of Nehemiah the governor, and of Ezra the priest, the scribe.
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'Now at the dedication of the wall of Jerusalem they sought out the
        Levites in all their places, to bring them to Jerusalem to celebrate the
        dedication with gladness, both with thanksgivings and singing, with cymbals
        and stringed instruments and harps. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'And the sons of the singers gathered together from the countryside
        around Jerusalem, from the villages of the Netophathites, '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'from the house of Gilgal, and from the fields of Geba and Azmaveth;
        for the singers had built themselves villages all around Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: Then the priests and Levites purified themselves, and purified the
        people, the gates, and the wall.
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'So I brought the leaders of Judah up on the wall, and appointed two
        large thanksgiving choirs. One went to the right hand on the wall toward
        the Refuse Gate. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'After them went Hoshaiah and half of the leaders of Judah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'and Azariah, Ezra, Meshullam, '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'Judah, Benjamin, Shemaiah, Jeremiah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "and some of the priests\u2019 sons with trumpets\u2014Zechariah the
        son of Jonathan, the son of Shemaiah, the son of Mattaniah, the son of Michaiah,
        the son of Zaccur, the son of Asaph, "
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'and his brethren, Shemaiah, Azarel, Milalai, Gilalai, Maai, Nethanel,
        Judah, and Hanani, with the musical instruments of David the man of God.
        Ezra the scribe went before them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: By the Fountain Gate, in front of them, they went up the stairs of
        the City of David, on the stairway of the wall, beyond the house of David,
        as far as the Water Gate eastward.
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'The other thanksgiving choir went the opposite way, and I was behind
        them with half of the people on the wall, going past the Tower of the Ovens
        as far as the Broad Wall, '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: and above the Gate of Ephraim, above the Old Gate, above the Fish
        Gate, the Tower of Hananel, the Tower of the Hundred, as far as the Sheep
        Gate; and they stopped by the Gate of the Prison.
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: 'So the two thanksgiving choirs stood in the house of God, likewise
        I and the half of the rulers with me; '
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: 'and the priests, Eliakim, Maaseiah, Minjamin, Michaiah, Elioenai,
        Zechariah, and Hananiah, with trumpets; '
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: also Maaseiah, Shemaiah, Eleazar, Uzzi, Jehohanan, Malchijah, Elam,
        and Ezer. The singers sang loudly with Jezrahiah the director.
      comments: []
    - name: '43: Temple Responsibilities'
      title: Temple Responsibilities
      number: 43
      content: Also that day they offered great sacrifices, and rejoiced, for God
        had made them rejoice with great joy; the women and the children also rejoiced,
        so that the joy of Jerusalem was heard afar off.
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: 'And at the same time some were appointed over the rooms of the storehouse
        for the offerings, the firstfruits, and the tithes, to gather into them from
        the fields of the cities the portions specified by the Law for the priests
        and Levites; for Judah rejoiced over the priests and Levites who ministered. '
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: 'Both the singers and the gatekeepers kept the charge of their God
        and the charge of the purification, according to the command of David and
        Solomon his son. '
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: 'For in the days of David and Asaph of old there  were chiefs of the
        singers, and songs of praise and thanksgiving to God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '47: '
      title: 
      number: 47
      content: In the days of Zerubbabel and in the days of Nehemiah all Israel gave
        the portions for the singers and the gatekeepers, a portion for each day.
        They also consecrated holy  things for the Levites, and the Levites consecrated
        them for the children of Aaron.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Principles of Separation'
      title: Principles of Separation
      number: 1
      content: 'On that day they read from the Book of Moses in the hearing of the
        people, and in it was found written that no Ammonite or Moabite should ever
        come into the assembly of God, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'because they had not met the children of Israel with bread and water,
        but hired Balaam against them to curse them. However, our God turned the
        curse into a blessing. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: The Reforms of Nehemiah'
      title: The Reforms of Nehemiah
      number: 3
      content: So it was, when they had heard the Law, that they separated all the
        mixed multitude from Israel.
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Now before this, Eliashib the priest, having authority over the storerooms
        of the house of our God, was allied with Tobiah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And he had prepared for him a large room, where previously they had
        stored the grain offerings, the frankincense, the articles, the tithes of
        grain, the new wine and oil, which were commanded to  be  given to the Levites
        and singers and gatekeepers, and the offerings for the priests. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'But during all this I was not in Jerusalem, for in the thirty-second
        year of Artaxerxes king of Babylon I had returned to the king. Then after
        certain days I obtained leave from the king, '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'and I came to Jerusalem and discovered the evil that Eliashib had
        done for Tobiah, in preparing a room for him in the courts of the house of
        God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And it grieved me bitterly; therefore I threw all the household goods
        of Tobiah out of the room. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: Then I commanded them to cleanse the rooms; and I brought back into
        them the articles of the house of God, with the grain offering and the frankincense.
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'I also realized that the portions for the Levites had not been given
        them; for each of the Levites and the singers who did the work had gone back
        to his field. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "So I contended with the rulers, and said, \u201CWhy is the house
        of God forsaken?\u201D And I gathered them together and set them in their
        place. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Then all Judah brought the tithe of the grain and the new wine and
        the oil to the storehouse. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: And I appointed as treasurers over the storehouse Shelemiah the priest
        and Zadok the scribe, and of the Levites, Pedaiah; and next to them was Hanan
        the son of Zaccur, the son of Mattaniah; for they were considered faithful,
        and their task was to distribute to their brethren.
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: Remember me, O my God, concerning this, and do not wipe out my good
        deeds that I have done for the house of my God, and for its services!
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'In those days I saw people in Judah treading wine presses on the
        Sabbath, and bringing in sheaves, and loading donkeys with wine, grapes,
        figs, and all kinds  of burdens, which they brought into Jerusalem on the
        Sabbath day. And I warned them about the day on which they were selling provisions. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: Men of Tyre dwelt there also, who brought in fish and all kinds of
        goods, and sold them on the Sabbath to the children of Judah, and in Jerusalem.
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Then I contended with the nobles of Judah, and said to them, \u201CWhat
        evil thing is this that you do, by which you profane the Sabbath day? "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Did not your fathers do thus, and did not our God bring all this
        disaster on us and on this city? Yet you bring added wrath on Israel by profaning
        the Sabbath.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'So it was, at the gates of Jerusalem, as it began to be dark before
        the Sabbath, that I commanded the gates to be shut, and charged that they
        must not be opened till after the Sabbath. Then I posted some of my servants
        at the gates, so  that no burdens would be brought in on the Sabbath day. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: Now the merchants and sellers of all kinds of wares lodged outside
        Jerusalem once or twice.
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Then I warned them, and said to them, \u201CWhy do you spend the
        night around the wall? If you do so again, I will lay hands on you!\u201D
        From that time on they came no more on the Sabbath. "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: And I commanded the Levites that they should cleanse themselves, and
        that they should go and guard the gates, to sanctify the Sabbath day.Remember
        me, O my God, concerning this also, and spare me according to the greatness
        of Your mercy!
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'In those days I also saw Jews who  had married women of Ashdod, Ammon,
        and Moab. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: And half of their children spoke the language of Ashdod, and could
        not speak the language of Judah, but spoke according to the language of one
        or the other people.
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "So I contended with them and cursed them, struck some of them and
        pulled out their hair, and made them swear by God, saying, \u201CYou shall
        not give your daughters as wives to their sons, nor take their daughters
        for your sons or yourselves. "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Did not Solomon king of Israel sin by these things? Yet among many
        nations there was no king like him, who was beloved of his God; and God made
        him king over all Israel. Nevertheless pagan women caused even him to sin. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "Should we then hear of your doing all this great evil, transgressing
        against our God by marrying pagan women?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: And one of the sons of Joiada, the son of Eliashib the high priest,
        was a son-in-law of Sanballat the Horonite; therefore I drove him from me.
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: Remember them, O my God, because they have defiled the priesthood
        and the covenant of the priesthood and the Levites.
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'Thus I cleansed them of everything pagan. I also assigned duties
        to the priests and the Levites, each to his service, '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: and to  bringing  the wood offering and the firstfruits at appointed
        times.Remember me, O my God, for good!
      comments: []
